{"id":209,"date":"2014-03-17T20:49:02","date_gmt":"2014-03-17T20:49:02","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/rstp.fantomdesign.net\/?page_id=209"},"modified":"2018-06-01T04:24:25","modified_gmt":"2018-06-01T08:24:25","slug":"about-the-rstp","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.rstp.ca\/en\/about-the-rstp\/","title":{"rendered":"About the RSTP"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The Refugee Sponsorship Training Program (RSTP) is a program designed to support the Sponsorship Agreement Holders (SAHs) of Canada, their Constituent Groups, Groups of Five and Community Sponsors on a national level (excl. Quebec). The objective of the RSTP is to address their information and on-going training needs as well as the initial information needs of sponsored refugees.<\/p>\n<p>The RSTP works closely with the SAH Council and the broader sponsorship community. It is supported by an <strong>Advisory Committee<\/strong>, who represent the various voices of the diverse SAH community across the Pacific, Prairies, Atlantic and central Canada (excl. Quebec). The committee provides guidance and planning assistance to the RSTP.<\/p>\n<p>RSTP is funded by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cic.gc.ca\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada<\/a> (IRCC) and administered by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cathcrosscultural.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Catholic Crosscultural Services (CCS)<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Refugee Sponsorship Training Program (RSTP) is a program designed to support the Sponsorship Agreement Holders (SAHs) of Canada, their Constituent Groups, Groups of Five and Community Sponsors on a [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_relevanssi_hide_post":"","_relevanssi_hide_content":"","_relevanssi_pin_for_all":"","_relevanssi_pin_keywords":"","_relevanssi_unpin_keywords":"","_rel